line_1: Come Rosalind, O, come! My brinded Kine,
line_2: My snowy Sheep, my Farm, and all is thine.

line_1: 'Twas there he milk'd his brindled Kine,
line_2: And there he fed his harmless Swine:

line_1: Like Sheep in grassy Meads, or fat'ning Kine
line_2: They chew the Cud, and on the Tast refine.
